{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LFAZLXxfsCzivDUFbuqhh9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The controller doesn't have `--enable-snippet-annotations=true` flag, which means in v1.14.1, snippet annotations might be restricted. Let me check if there's a way to enable them, or if there's another approach.\n\nActually, in ingress-nginx 1.9+, there's a security change that requires `--enable-annotation-validation` to be set and snippet annotations to be explicitly enabled via a configuration. Let me check if `configuration-snippet` is blocked.\n\nActually, there are two flags:\n1. `--allow-snippet-annotations` (deprecated in some versions)\n2. The ConfigMap key `allow-snippet-annotations: \"true\"`\nBut since neither is present, snippet annotations are likely blocked. A better approach would be to use the global ConfigMap and set `limit-req-status-code` to \"429\" to establish this as the default for all rate-limited responses across the cluster. For the `configuration-snippet` issue, I could try using a `server-snippet` on the Ingress instead, though that's also a snippet annotation, so the ConfigMap approach is probably the cleanest solution here.\n\nLooking at the nginx-ingress documentation, I see `limit-req-status-code` can be configured either globally in the ConfigMap or via a per-Ingress annotation. Let me verify whether the annotation `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-req-status-code` actually exists in v1.14.1, since I want to make sure I'm using the right approach for this specific version.\n\nMy plan is to update the ConfigMap to set `limit-req-status-code: \"429\"` since that's the cleaner approach and won't require snippet annotations. The status code change only affects rate-limited responses, so it shouldn't impact the /health route which isn't rate limited. I need to verify how nginx-ingress applies rate limiting across multiple Ingress resources on the same host. Since each Ingress creates separate location blocks, I can configure `/api` with rate limiting and `/health` without it, and they'll be handled independently. Let me structure the two Ingresses accordingly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":574,"cache_read_input_tokens":43163,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":574},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"05deaebe-af88-4439-b66c-5774aca7c1be","uuid":"561ad53d-cd4e-4bf1-ae37-e97c298de03b","request_id":"req_011Cc6dmqYuRTsHGVpwXFUk7"}
