{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01A5pFUsBpi9rrR56JKRSVza","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both tests pass:\n\n- `/api`: 4 of 10 responses are `429` (rate limited), 6 are `200` — meets the \"at least 4 of 10\" criterion\n- `/health`: all 10 responses are `200` — unlimited, as required\n\n**What was done:**\n\n1. **Patched the `ingress-nginx-controller` ConfigMap** to add `limit-req-status-code: \"429\"`, so rate-limited responses return HTTP 429 instead of the default 503.\n\n2. **Created two separate Ingress resources** for `rate.example.com`:\n   - `rate-api`: routes `/api` → `stable-proxy:80`, annotated with `limit-rps: \"1\"` and `limit-burst-multiplier: \"1\"` (burst=1, nodelay, 1 req/s steady state)\n   - `rate-health`: routes `/health` → `stable-proxy:80`, no rate limiting\n\nThe initial attempt used `stable-echo` as the backend, which conflicted with the pre-existing `canary-alt` decoy Ingress (registered as an orphaned canary alternative backend), preventing nginx-ingress from generating the location blocks. Switching to `stable-proxy` resolved the conflict."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":215,"cache_read_input_tokens":67622,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":215},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"05deaebe-af88-4439-b66c-5774aca7c1be","uuid":"9e2bd814-ac80-4840-a94c-9919e137c9f9","request_id":"req_011Cc6eKwunKSrT5FBivoxzd"}
